A BILL ENTITLED
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Consumer Protection – Consumer Reporting Agencies – Use of Algorithmic
3 Systems
4 FOR the purpose of establishing requirements for consumer reporting agencies that use
5 algorithmic systems to assemble or evaluate consumer credit information on
6 consumers for the purpose of furnishing consumer reports to third parties; requiring
7 the Commissioner of Financial Regulation of the Maryland Department of Labor to
8 establish certain assessment thresholds for algorithms, mandate regular training for
9 human reviewers, and implement a certain whistleblower protection program; and
10 generally relating to consumer reporting agencies and algorithmic systems.
